00:07:30.150 --> 00:07:33.080
What I'm first interested in
hearing about is what kind of

00:07:33.080 --> 00:07:38.310
data is gathered by bitly
from your users.

00:07:38.310 --> 00:07:40.630
HILARY MASON: So we primarily
see three kinds of data.

00:07:40.630 --> 00:07:42.810
We see the save and
share events.

00:07:42.810 --> 00:07:46.480
So if somebody shortens a link
or saves it in bitly.com, we

00:07:46.480 --> 00:07:49.120
see the entire set of
clicks on that link

00:07:49.120 --> 00:07:50.630
once it's shared out.

00:07:50.630 --> 00:07:53.150
And that includes things like
the location of where people

00:07:53.150 --> 00:07:56.400
are clicking on things from,
their referral, which social

00:07:56.400 --> 00:07:59.410
network it's getting traffic
from, the user agent, so what

00:07:59.410 --> 00:08:01.420
kind of device and
stuff like that.

00:08:01.420 --> 00:08:03.880
And then we actually go
and crawl the full

00:08:03.880 --> 00:08:05.750
content of each link.

00:08:05.750 --> 00:08:08.170
And we would do a bunch of
analysis on that as well.

00:08:08.170 --> 00:08:11.230
So we primarily work with those
three types of data.

00:08:11.230 --> 00:08:11.690
KATHRYN HURLEY: OK.

00:08:11.690 --> 00:08:13.965
That's some pretty interesting
data that you gather.

00:08:13.965 --> 00:08:14.870
HILARY MASON: Definitely.

00:08:14.870 --> 00:08:16.300
KATHRYN HURLEY: Yeah.

00:08:16.300 --> 00:08:20.540
